The Eldorado Park community is in mourning following the brutal rape and murder of a four-year-old girl who went missing on Wednesday. According to reports, she went missing from 4pm. A search ensued for the missing infant, and after the four-hour search, her body was found in a drain at the koppie in Extension Two, Westside Eldos reported. A man believed to be the perpetrator of this gruesome act has been apprehended, and is in police custody. Residents say the man did not act alone, and until more facts on the case come to light, the community is in an uproar over the horrific way in which her young life was taken. Information remains sketchy at the moment, but an update will follow as soon as more details become available. – Caxton News Service Read original story on westside-eldos.co.za